ening introduction and the original Latin on facing pages, How to Give is a timeless guide to the profound significance of true generosity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aBenevolencevEarly works to 1800. 0aConduct of lifevEarly works to 1800. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aLatin prose style.  aLatin writers.  aRoman philosophy.  aSeneca the Younger.  aSeneca's life and times.  aadvice on gift giving.  aanthology.  abeneficia.  abeneficium.  abiography.  acontemporary translation.  aethics.  aetiquette.  afavor.  agift giving.  agraciousness.  agratia.  ahow to be gracious.  ahow to be grateful.  ahow to politely accept gifts.  ahow to show gratitude.  aimportance of generosity.  aintroduction to Seneca's thought.  amodern translation.  anew translation of Seneca.  aphilanthropy.  arhetoric.  arules of gift giving.  aselection.  aself help.  astoicism.  aunderstanding Seneca.  awritings.1 aRomm, James S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069008840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691211367zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691211367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691211367.jpg  a978-3-11-069008-8  PUP Frontlist eBook-Package 202